CatDescriptText: Sarah Burney, Schenley Heights and Delores Burney, Schenley Heights, were part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier Newspaper, September 3, 1960, pg. A1 with question "What is our country's most pressing domestic problem?"  Ms. S. Burney's answer reads: "Housing perhaps, is our most pressing problem.  People have a hard time finding a decent place to live."  Ms. D. Burney's answer reads: "There are so many pressing problems within our country that it would take many volumes to list."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Sarah Burney wearing light colored short sleeved shirt, standing on sidewalk with trees in background; Portrait of Delores Burney wearing light colored sleeveless blouse with rounded collar, seated in light colored car
